.TH "dynevent_arg_init" 9 "dynevent_arg_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dynevent_arg_init \- Initialize a dynevent_arg object
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" dynevent_arg_init
.BI "(struct dynevent_arg *arg "  ","
.BI "char separator "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "arg" 12
A pointer to the dynevent_arg struct representing the arg
.IP "separator" 12
An (optional) separator, appended after adding the arg
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Initialize a dynevent_arg object.  A dynevent_arg represents an
object used to append single arguments to the current command
string.  After the arg string is successfully appended to the
command string, the optional \fIseparator\fP is appended.  If no
separator was specified when initializing the arg, a space will be
appended.
